This paper discusses a meta-learning algorithm that combines parallel algorithms, ensemble, and boosting methodologies to achieve scalability without compromising the quality of results. The paper presents both theoretical and empirical analyses, which are common in the machine learning subfield of computer science (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between scalability and accuracy, which is relevant to the data structures and algorithms subfield (cs.DS). The use of boosting and ensemble methodologies is common in the artificial intelligence subfield (cs.AI) and the data mining subfield (cs.DM). Finally, the use of parallel algorithms is relevant to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing subfield (cs.CC).
